WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.200
Pray with me and for me really quick

2
00:00:02.200 --> 00:00:03.600
before I share my testimony.

3
00:00:05.680 --> 00:00:10.000
Heavenly Father, we, I'm so humbled

4
00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:11.720
to have the opportunity to share

5
00:00:12.800 --> 00:00:15.400
even just a part of my story.

6
00:00:15.400 --> 00:00:19.900
And I'm reminded that I am not really sharing my story

7
00:00:21.040 --> 00:00:23.180
but I'm sharing your story through me.

8
00:00:24.600 --> 00:00:28.600
The Lord let that be the story that is made known today.

9
00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:31.120
Jesus' name, amen.

10
00:00:34.280 --> 00:00:37.080
Last night, I was having a good conversation

11
00:00:37.080 --> 00:00:41.880
and was reminded that we are a story telling people.

12
00:00:42.720 --> 00:00:47.720
We enjoy telling stories, we enjoy listening to stories

13
00:00:48.520 --> 00:00:51.480
and most everything that you can think of

14
00:00:51.480 --> 00:00:54.880
is part of a story, whether that is your favorite

15
00:00:54.920 --> 00:00:58.840
movie series or your favorite TV show,

16
00:00:58.840 --> 00:01:01.440
sports that you like to watch or anything,

17
00:01:01.440 --> 00:01:03.360
it's all a narrative.

18
00:01:03.360 --> 00:01:05.240
And I think that's what makes it so compelling

19
00:01:05.240 --> 00:01:07.720
and so enjoyable is because it is a narrative.

20
00:01:08.720 --> 00:01:13.280
We were created to love and speak through narrative.

21
00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:15.960
I think that's the power of telling stories.

22
00:01:15.960 --> 00:01:18.080
And what's interesting is that the Bible

23
00:01:18.080 --> 00:01:21.240
is not merely a list of rules or facts or things to do

24
00:01:21.240 --> 00:01:23.540
but it is written as a narrative.

25
00:01:25.720 --> 00:01:30.720
We love stories and we find our significance in stories.

26
00:01:31.160 --> 00:01:33.320
A quote that I really love, at the time I heard it,

27
00:01:33.320 --> 00:01:34.720
it was attributed to Wendell Berry.

28
00:01:34.720 --> 00:01:36.840
I was not able to find it so I can't quote it

29
00:01:36.840 --> 00:01:40.120
exactly for you but I will try and recall it

30
00:01:40.120 --> 00:01:41.600
to the best of my ability because it's stuck

31
00:01:41.600 --> 00:01:43.900
with me since then and it's that people find

32
00:01:43.900 --> 00:01:46.080
their significance from the biggest story

33
00:01:46.080 --> 00:01:48.720
in which they see themselves as playing a role.

34
00:01:49.720 --> 00:01:54.720
And so for me, as I recount God's story through me,

35
00:01:55.960 --> 00:02:00.360
I think the main point that I wanna communicate

36
00:02:00.360 --> 00:02:02.480
is that at different points in my life,

37
00:02:02.480 --> 00:02:06.440
I have believed that the biggest story I was a part of

38
00:02:06.440 --> 00:02:10.480
was not the one that really is the biggest story

39
00:02:10.480 --> 00:02:12.320
which is God's story.

40
00:02:12.320 --> 00:02:15.080
And that lie of believing these other stories

41
00:02:15.600 --> 00:02:19.800
is ultimately what I needed to be saved from

42
00:02:19.800 --> 00:02:23.320
that my sin ultimately flowed out of me believing

43
00:02:23.320 --> 00:02:26.360
that these other stories were more important than God himself.

44
00:02:27.600 --> 00:02:31.440
So the question I have asked or asked myself

45
00:02:31.440 --> 00:02:33.160
and the question I'll ask for you today

46
00:02:33.160 --> 00:02:35.320
as I tell my story is what is the story

47
00:02:35.320 --> 00:02:37.960
that you are believing is the biggest right now

48
00:02:37.960 --> 00:02:41.400
in your life and where do you see yourself playing a role?

49
00:02:41.400 --> 00:02:46.400
In my story, I'm blessed to say that I've never known a time

50
00:02:47.600 --> 00:02:50.920
where I didn't know who God was.

51
00:02:50.920 --> 00:02:53.920
I was raised in a Christian family,

52
00:02:53.920 --> 00:02:55.800
parents who loved the Lord.

53
00:02:55.800 --> 00:02:58.080
We were involved in church very regularly

54
00:02:59.080 --> 00:03:01.120
but there are several stories I find myself

55
00:03:01.120 --> 00:03:02.640
frequently chasing after.

56
00:03:03.640 --> 00:03:07.920
The first one is one that says basically,

57
00:03:07.920 --> 00:03:12.000
I am trying to maximize my own pleasure

58
00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:14.080
and minimize the pain that I get.

59
00:03:14.080 --> 00:03:17.400
And that's somehow the story or the game that I am playing,

60
00:03:17.400 --> 00:03:19.600
the thing that I want to do the most.

61
00:03:19.600 --> 00:03:20.880
And so what does that look like?

62
00:03:20.880 --> 00:03:24.320
Well, in practice, for me, as I was growing up,

63
00:03:24.320 --> 00:03:28.160
I would think outwardly as a people pleaser

64
00:03:28.160 --> 00:03:29.760
in the Bible belt, I'm gonna make sure

65
00:03:29.760 --> 00:03:32.720
that my life looks like it is good,

66
00:03:33.640 --> 00:03:36.440
that I'm going to follow the rules,

67
00:03:36.480 --> 00:03:38.840
I'm not going to stand out too much,

68
00:03:38.840 --> 00:03:42.560
I don't wanna be noticed and I don't wanna be really known.

69
00:03:42.560 --> 00:03:46.040
And so growing up, that's how I lived is in high school,

70
00:03:46.040 --> 00:03:48.800
I really didn't want to be the one that was standing

71
00:03:48.800 --> 00:03:51.520
in front of a group of people sharing anything.

72
00:03:51.520 --> 00:03:54.880
So even standing up here is kind of out of my comfort zone.

73
00:03:58.760 --> 00:04:03.760
That kind of lie that my story is just this side thing

74
00:04:04.720 --> 00:04:06.040
that doesn't really matter.

75
00:04:06.040 --> 00:04:08.680
It's not really a part of anything else.

76
00:04:08.680 --> 00:04:12.400
That lie led to a lot of depression, anxiety.

77
00:04:12.400 --> 00:04:14.360
In fact, in high school, I actually dropped out

78
00:04:14.360 --> 00:04:16.480
of high school, I never graduated.

79
00:04:17.600 --> 00:04:20.760
The depression of just not really finding

80
00:04:20.760 --> 00:04:25.680
my significance anywhere led to why does this even matter?

81
00:04:25.680 --> 00:04:30.680
Lots of questions of self-worth of anxiety

82
00:04:31.120 --> 00:04:36.120
and it led to a lot of hiding whatever pain I had,

83
00:04:37.200 --> 00:04:39.160
just trying to hide it away,

84
00:04:39.160 --> 00:04:42.640
not letting it be known because at the end of the day,

85
00:04:42.640 --> 00:04:45.680
I wanted other people to think that I had it all together

86
00:04:45.680 --> 00:04:48.480
because that was the story where I found my significance.

87
00:04:50.460 --> 00:04:54.640
I believed that I was the main character of my story,

88
00:04:55.920 --> 00:05:00.120
that somehow I could do XYZ to earn other people's approval

89
00:05:00.120 --> 00:05:03.120
and that doing that would ultimately bring joy

90
00:05:03.120 --> 00:05:04.960
and yet it did not.

91
00:05:06.200 --> 00:05:09.520
The end result of chasing that pleasure in secret

92
00:05:09.520 --> 00:05:11.920
while projecting to other stability

93
00:05:11.920 --> 00:05:16.600
was at the end of the day, depression and falling apart.

94
00:05:16.600 --> 00:05:18.920
But no one else would know that.

95
00:05:18.920 --> 00:05:21.560
I kept it hidden pretty well.

96
00:05:21.560 --> 00:05:23.480
My sister might beg to differ.

97
00:05:24.760 --> 00:05:26.200
She might have noticed it more than others

98
00:05:26.200 --> 00:05:30.440
but at the end of the day, that's kind of who I was.

99
00:05:30.440 --> 00:05:33.280
Dropped out of high school, I got my GED,

100
00:05:33.280 --> 00:05:35.480
started working immediately and thought then that,

101
00:05:35.480 --> 00:05:38.960
oh, well this extra income can then provide extra pleasures.

102
00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:41.400
So why don't I chase after those?

103
00:05:41.400 --> 00:05:43.400
Because maybe the problem is that I'm not

104
00:05:43.400 --> 00:05:46.000
finding enough pleasure or the right pleasures.

105
00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:48.240
So I started trying to go down every avenue

106
00:05:48.240 --> 00:05:51.760
you could possibly think of chasing what that looked like.

107
00:05:52.320 --> 00:05:57.480
At one point, I point back to this time because

108
00:05:58.920 --> 00:06:02.440
there was a time where I was in a car with a friend

109
00:06:02.440 --> 00:06:05.080
and we were going off to do something I can't remember.

110
00:06:05.080 --> 00:06:06.200
We lived together at the time

111
00:06:06.200 --> 00:06:08.880
and I remember turning to him and thinking like

112
00:06:08.880 --> 00:06:10.920
something in my mind just changed

113
00:06:10.920 --> 00:06:13.560
and I can't put an explanation on this

114
00:06:13.560 --> 00:06:16.000
other than to say that God at some point just said,

115
00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:19.920
you are mine, I have chosen you for a bigger story

116
00:06:19.920 --> 00:06:20.760
than this one.

117
00:06:22.400 --> 00:06:23.440
I turned to him and said,

118
00:06:23.440 --> 00:06:28.360
I can't continue whatever it is we're doing.

119
00:06:28.360 --> 00:06:30.240
And it really confused him at the time

120
00:06:30.240 --> 00:06:32.160
because I don't know that either of us

121
00:06:32.160 --> 00:06:34.320
had really consciously decided to go off

122
00:06:34.320 --> 00:06:36.980
on this side tangent of living our own stories.

123
00:06:38.280 --> 00:06:39.840
But at that point, at that moment,

124
00:06:39.840 --> 00:06:41.900
I can say honestly that that was the turning point

125
00:06:41.900 --> 00:06:44.520
in my life where God himself reached into my life

126
00:06:44.520 --> 00:06:49.000
and told me I have called you

127
00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:50.700
to something greater than this.

128
00:06:52.760 --> 00:06:57.040
But contrary to what you might think

129
00:06:57.040 --> 00:07:00.200
when you see stories in various movies

130
00:07:00.200 --> 00:07:02.000
where the turning point all of a sudden turns

131
00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:03.760
into this glorious return,

132
00:07:03.760 --> 00:07:07.100
that's not exactly how my story went

133
00:07:07.100 --> 00:07:08.560
because it took a while.

134
00:07:08.560 --> 00:07:12.480
You see the path to following Christ

135
00:07:12.480 --> 00:07:15.680
didn't immediately unfold before me.

136
00:07:16.600 --> 00:07:18.720
I still was drawn to this story

137
00:07:18.720 --> 00:07:20.580
and still believed in my heart

138
00:07:20.620 --> 00:07:22.780
that at the end of the day,

139
00:07:22.780 --> 00:07:25.660
I'm kind of this side character,

140
00:07:25.660 --> 00:07:27.260
this person over here,

141
00:07:27.260 --> 00:07:30.020
God's story and who Jesus was

142
00:07:31.620 --> 00:07:33.620
is not a part of my story.

143
00:07:33.620 --> 00:07:36.580
Like those are different things that disconnected.

144
00:07:36.580 --> 00:07:37.980
And because I believed that,

145
00:07:37.980 --> 00:07:40.140
I would follow Christ and try to go

146
00:07:40.140 --> 00:07:42.700
and learn, read the Bible,

147
00:07:42.700 --> 00:07:45.580
and then continue to try and do my side project

148
00:07:45.580 --> 00:07:47.940
of well maybe I can try and maximize pleasure

149
00:07:47.940 --> 00:07:50.100
and minimize pain in other ways.

150
00:07:50.140 --> 00:07:52.380
Specifically on the minimizing pain front

151
00:07:52.380 --> 00:07:55.060
that became like my main goal

152
00:07:55.060 --> 00:07:58.540
is this side project of I'm going to

153
00:07:58.540 --> 00:08:00.580
lose myself in video games

154
00:08:00.580 --> 00:08:02.460
or I am going to lose myself

155
00:08:02.460 --> 00:08:05.180
in binge watching TV

156
00:08:05.180 --> 00:08:07.300
rather than focusing on the goal

157
00:08:07.300 --> 00:08:08.580
that God has set before me

158
00:08:08.580 --> 00:08:12.180
which was taking up my cross and following Jesus.

159
00:08:16.860 --> 00:08:19.140
At the end of the day, return was not easy

160
00:08:19.140 --> 00:08:22.100
because I was still trying to do it by myself.

161
00:08:23.500 --> 00:08:26.700
In spoil alert, you cannot do it on your own.

162
00:08:28.740 --> 00:08:30.820
Beyond the obvious that Jesus is the one

163
00:08:30.820 --> 00:08:33.540
that paid the price for us and you need him,

164
00:08:33.540 --> 00:08:37.260
you also need each other.

165
00:08:37.260 --> 00:08:41.260
And I needed someone else

166
00:08:41.260 --> 00:08:44.660
or other people to talk to

167
00:08:44.660 --> 00:08:47.420
about the things that I was trying to hide for so long.

168
00:08:50.020 --> 00:08:54.500
Around my junior year of, I guess senior year,

169
00:08:54.500 --> 00:08:55.860
going into senior year of college,

170
00:08:55.860 --> 00:08:57.140
I had a broken engagement

171
00:08:58.420 --> 00:09:02.780
where I feel like I fell finally to rock bottom.

172
00:09:02.780 --> 00:09:05.540
This was after the turning point in my life.

173
00:09:05.540 --> 00:09:08.100
I remember the conversation that happened before.

174
00:09:08.100 --> 00:09:11.220
Like I feel like rock bottom happened after that

175
00:09:11.220 --> 00:09:12.180
which is interesting.

176
00:09:12.180 --> 00:09:14.100
I don't know necessarily what to do that still

177
00:09:14.100 --> 00:09:17.020
with this story and my story is still being written.

178
00:09:17.060 --> 00:09:20.660
And yet at that point, I remember distinctly opening up

179
00:09:20.660 --> 00:09:23.420
and talking to other people about what was going on

180
00:09:23.420 --> 00:09:26.220
in my heart and not just what I wanted them to see.

181
00:09:27.740 --> 00:09:30.740
And that confession of what was really happening

182
00:09:30.740 --> 00:09:35.740
in my life started to change my heart.

183
00:09:36.620 --> 00:09:39.200
It was a slow healing process after that.

184
00:09:40.780 --> 00:09:44.380
I remember I spent about a year of just walking around

185
00:09:44.380 --> 00:09:48.420
Samford University's campus probably every night.

186
00:09:48.420 --> 00:09:49.460
It's really calm.

187
00:09:49.460 --> 00:09:52.100
It's a great place to walk if you ever want to.

188
00:09:52.100 --> 00:09:54.260
But that's what I did as I walked around their campus

189
00:09:54.260 --> 00:09:56.780
probably every night for about a year.

190
00:09:57.660 --> 00:10:02.100
I remember even the song we sang this morning,

191
00:10:02.100 --> 00:10:03.300
I stand amazed.

192
00:10:03.300 --> 00:10:06.740
I would sing songs in my head as I was walking

193
00:10:06.740 --> 00:10:09.260
and I remember God just continually telling me

194
00:10:09.260 --> 00:10:10.580
and comforting me that like,

195
00:10:11.580 --> 00:10:15.260
he was telling me that you are a part of my story.

196
00:10:16.980 --> 00:10:20.140
You play a significant role in my story.

197
00:10:21.100 --> 00:10:26.100
You are not a side character that does not have any purpose.

198
00:10:26.860 --> 00:10:29.980
I have called you for something greater

199
00:10:29.980 --> 00:10:32.060
and I want you to follow me.

200
00:10:35.180 --> 00:10:37.620
Slowly over time after that,

201
00:10:37.700 --> 00:10:40.560
and for the past six or seven years,

202
00:10:41.660 --> 00:10:43.860
that has become more and more meaningful to me.

203
00:10:48.580 --> 00:10:52.160
I guess in closing with my story,

204
00:10:54.620 --> 00:10:58.780
I really just want to recount to you what God's story is

205
00:10:59.580 --> 00:11:04.100
rather than focus on how God has done anything through me.

206
00:11:05.060 --> 00:11:07.020
And I was reminded of that as we sang

207
00:11:07.020 --> 00:11:08.940
before the throne as well.

208
00:11:08.940 --> 00:11:11.620
I'm just gonna read these words back

209
00:11:11.620 --> 00:11:13.760
because I think it's worth just pausing and meditating

210
00:11:13.760 --> 00:11:15.620
on what this actually means.

211
00:11:16.940 --> 00:11:20.180
It says, because the sinless Savior died,

212
00:11:20.180 --> 00:11:22.900
my sinful soul is counted free.

213
00:11:23.780 --> 00:11:28.460
For God the just is satisfied to look on him

214
00:11:28.460 --> 00:11:29.500
and pardon me.

215
00:11:31.020 --> 00:11:33.620
And at the end of the day, I didn't do anything

216
00:11:34.620 --> 00:11:37.140
to earn that pardon.

217
00:11:38.180 --> 00:11:42.460
And yet God has looked on me.

218
00:11:51.060 --> 00:11:53.220
It's hard to imagine because I really didn't deserve

219
00:11:53.220 --> 00:11:54.140
any of this.

220
00:11:55.460 --> 00:11:58.340
I know many of us in the room probably feel the same way.

221
00:11:58.340 --> 00:11:59.660
I would just leave us with a couple of things.

222
00:11:59.700 --> 00:12:04.700
One is I continue to sit with the question

223
00:12:06.380 --> 00:12:09.580
of what is the story that I'm believing day in and day out?

224
00:12:09.580 --> 00:12:11.980
It's one of the questions I ask myself every day

225
00:12:11.980 --> 00:12:13.620
because I find myself consistently falling

226
00:12:13.620 --> 00:12:15.380
into the old patterns of my life.

227
00:12:19.620 --> 00:12:24.180
But also knowing that at the end of the day

228
00:12:24.180 --> 00:12:27.940
it's God's story that I am a part of.

229
00:12:27.980 --> 00:12:29.740
And my part matters.

230
00:12:29.740 --> 00:12:31.060
And your part matters.

231
00:12:32.100 --> 00:12:34.140
He knows you specifically.

232
00:12:38.580 --> 00:12:40.140
He's called you specifically.

233
00:12:43.700 --> 00:12:47.540
So for me the call was to come out of hiding

234
00:12:47.540 --> 00:12:49.460
whatever it is I was trying to hide

235
00:12:50.580 --> 00:12:52.060
and to be an authentic person.

236
00:12:53.300 --> 00:12:57.060
To live in following who Jesus is.

237
00:12:58.940 --> 00:13:01.100
So each and every day that's the goal.

238
00:13:01.100 --> 00:13:03.460
Obviously I fall far short of that every day.

239
00:13:03.460 --> 00:13:08.460
But I'm always reminded that it's God's grace in my life.

240
00:13:10.060 --> 00:13:10.900
Thank you.

241
00:13:19.740 --> 00:13:21.700
Okay, thank you so much for sharing that.

242
00:13:21.700 --> 00:13:25.820
We really appreciate your openness and what you shared.

243
00:13:26.380 --> 00:13:28.540
So grateful that the Lord in this story

244
00:13:28.540 --> 00:13:31.500
has brought you and Mary into the life of this church

245
00:13:31.500 --> 00:13:33.380
as well as the kids too.

246
00:13:33.380 --> 00:13:36.420
Let's turn together to Psalm 6.

247
00:13:36.420 --> 00:13:37.540
Psalm 6.

248
00:13:41.580 --> 00:13:43.780
Much of what we were just hearing,

249
00:13:43.780 --> 00:13:46.100
we hear in David's own story,

250
00:13:46.100 --> 00:13:48.140
the author of this Psalm.

251
00:13:48.140 --> 00:13:52.100
This points us to the Lord's story.

252
00:13:53.060 --> 00:13:55.380
So I'll read Psalm 6.

253
00:13:55.420 --> 00:13:57.500
And we'll pray and walk through this together.

254
00:13:59.180 --> 00:14:02.660
Oh Lord, rebuke me not in your anger,

255
00:14:02.660 --> 00:14:05.180
nor discipline me in your wrath.

256
00:14:05.180 --> 00:14:09.260
Be gracious to me, oh Lord, for I am languishing.

257
00:14:09.260 --> 00:14:13.780
Heal me, oh Lord, for my bones are troubled.

258
00:14:13.780 --> 00:14:17.340
My soul is also greatly troubled.

259
00:14:17.340 --> 00:14:20.140
But you, oh Lord, how long?

260
00:14:21.140 --> 00:14:24.180
Turn, oh Lord, deliver my life.

261
00:14:24.180 --> 00:14:27.820
Save me for the sake of your steadfast love,

262
00:14:27.820 --> 00:14:30.620
for in death there is no remembrance of you.

263
00:14:30.620 --> 00:14:33.700
And, Shale, who will give you praise?

264
00:14:33.700 --> 00:14:38.700
I am weary with my moaning every night I flood my bed with tears.

265
00:14:38.700 --> 00:14:41.180
I drench my couch with weeping.

266
00:14:41.180 --> 00:14:44.980
My eye wastes away because of grief.

267
00:14:44.980 --> 00:14:49.220
It grows weak because of all my foes.

268
00:14:49.820 --> 00:14:52.580
Depart from me all you workers of evil,

269
00:14:52.580 --> 00:14:56.060
for the Lord has heard the sound of my weeping.

270
00:14:56.060 --> 00:14:58.620
The Lord has heard my plea.

271
00:14:58.620 --> 00:15:01.100
The Lord accepts my prayer.

272
00:15:01.100 --> 00:15:05.580
All my enemies shall be ashamed and greatly troubled.

273
00:15:05.580 --> 00:15:09.500
They shall turn back and be put to shame in a moment.

274
00:15:09.500 --> 00:15:11.060
This is the word of the Lord.

275
00:15:13.420 --> 00:15:16.140
So Lord, I pray that you would speak to us now

276
00:15:16.140 --> 00:15:18.300
for your servants are listening.

277
00:15:18.740 --> 00:15:19.580
Amen.

278
00:15:21.100 --> 00:15:23.060
If you've never come across

279
00:15:23.060 --> 00:15:27.340
the Japanese-American artist Makoto Fujimura,

280
00:15:27.340 --> 00:15:31.140
I would very much encourage you to look at some of his artwork.

281
00:15:31.140 --> 00:15:32.620
I'm sure I pronounced his name wrong,

282
00:15:32.620 --> 00:15:34.260
just in case you're wondering that too.

283
00:15:34.260 --> 00:15:36.700
But he's a painter based in New York City,

284
00:15:36.700 --> 00:15:38.780
but he's also written a number of helpful things

285
00:15:38.780 --> 00:15:42.580
on the connection between art and faith.

286
00:15:42.580 --> 00:15:44.260
And one thing that he's written about

287
00:15:45.020 --> 00:15:48.780
is this Japanese art form called kinsugi.

288
00:15:48.780 --> 00:15:53.780
Now kinsugi is basically the art of repairing broken pottery.

289
00:15:54.460 --> 00:15:57.740
And actually the word is a combination of two words.

290
00:15:57.740 --> 00:15:59.100
And one of the words is mending

291
00:15:59.100 --> 00:16:01.220
and the other word is gold.

292
00:16:01.220 --> 00:16:03.420
So basically like when a ceramic bowl is broken,

293
00:16:03.420 --> 00:16:04.980
instead of throwing it away,

294
00:16:04.980 --> 00:16:07.980
you would save that bowl because one day

295
00:16:07.980 --> 00:16:09.940
you'll then either bring that to an artist

296
00:16:09.940 --> 00:16:12.340
or you're the artist and you'll then take that

297
00:16:12.340 --> 00:16:13.900
and you will mend it.

298
00:16:13.900 --> 00:16:15.860
And instead of mending it in such a way,

299
00:16:15.860 --> 00:16:17.260
like you would say like super glue

300
00:16:17.260 --> 00:16:18.780
where you don't wanna see the cracks anymore

301
00:16:18.780 --> 00:16:21.380
towards trying to get it back to that perfect condition,

302
00:16:21.380 --> 00:16:24.340
what's done instead is they produce a lacquer

303
00:16:24.340 --> 00:16:27.660
which is mixed with gold and they do it in such a way

304
00:16:27.660 --> 00:16:30.420
that you can still see exactly where the cracks were,

305
00:16:30.420 --> 00:16:33.700
but now it's joined together by this lacquer and this gold.

306
00:16:33.700 --> 00:16:36.740
And so that is now even more valuable

307
00:16:36.740 --> 00:16:38.420
than it was before it was broken.

308
00:16:38.420 --> 00:16:40.120
And it's there not to be discarded,

309
00:16:40.120 --> 00:16:43.700
but to be passed on to future generations.

310
00:16:43.700 --> 00:16:47.780
So through the brokenness comes beauty.

311
00:16:49.260 --> 00:16:52.860
And this is what we see in Psalm six.

312
00:16:52.860 --> 00:16:56.700
David is before us as a man who is utterly broken,

313
00:16:56.700 --> 00:16:59.220
but his story isn't over

314
00:16:59.220 --> 00:17:02.540
because God takes the broken pieces of his life

315
00:17:02.540 --> 00:17:05.780
and he creates something beautiful

316
00:17:05.780 --> 00:17:09.460
that will bless generations to come,

317
00:17:09.460 --> 00:17:12.440
including us sitting here this morning.

318
00:17:12.480 --> 00:17:16.640
So it's on display here for us in Psalm six.

319
00:17:16.640 --> 00:17:18.960
And as we look at this together,

320
00:17:18.960 --> 00:17:22.320
we see the God who did this in David's life

321
00:17:22.320 --> 00:17:24.320
and we can know that he can do the same thing

322
00:17:24.320 --> 00:17:25.860
in ours as well.

323
00:17:26.720 --> 00:17:29.000
He can take our brokenness

324
00:17:29.000 --> 00:17:31.320
and create something beautiful.

325
00:17:32.360 --> 00:17:33.200
So with that in view,

326
00:17:33.200 --> 00:17:35.800
we're gonna learn about David's distress,

327
00:17:35.800 --> 00:17:37.760
what he was going through,

328
00:17:37.760 --> 00:17:40.600
but we're also gonna see what he does with his distress

329
00:17:41.040 --> 00:17:43.080
as he brings this before the Lord.

330
00:17:43.080 --> 00:17:45.680
And then finally we'll see what the Lord then does

331
00:17:45.680 --> 00:17:49.440
with the broken pieces of his life, so to speak.

332
00:17:49.440 --> 00:17:53.480
So what kind of distress is David experiencing?

333
00:17:53.480 --> 00:17:55.840
All right, so a couple of weeks ago,

334
00:17:55.840 --> 00:17:59.520
we saw in Psalm four that there is joy to be had

335
00:17:59.520 --> 00:18:02.880
and David knew what it was like to rejoice in the Lord

336
00:18:02.880 --> 00:18:04.840
and the joy that he knew was greater

337
00:18:04.840 --> 00:18:07.880
than the other people he recognized around him.

338
00:18:08.880 --> 00:18:13.880
So there's a deep joy for us to know as followers of Christ,

339
00:18:13.880 --> 00:18:17.080
but that does not mean that the Christian life is

340
00:18:17.080 --> 00:18:20.080
all smiles all the time.

341
00:18:20.080 --> 00:18:24.760
And to pretend that it is would only breed hypocrisy.

342
00:18:24.760 --> 00:18:26.760
The fact is is that this side of eternity,

343
00:18:26.760 --> 00:18:29.960
we live in a broken world.

344
00:18:29.960 --> 00:18:33.720
And so we will experience the pain and the sorrow

345
00:18:33.720 --> 00:18:35.400
that comes with that brokenness.

346
00:18:36.400 --> 00:18:39.400
I love what Zach S. Wein said.

347
00:18:39.400 --> 00:18:44.400
He said, in this fallen world, sadness is an act of sanity.

348
00:18:45.400 --> 00:18:49.400
Our tears, the testimony of the sane.

349
00:18:49.400 --> 00:18:52.400
In other words, it's a reflection of the broken reality

350
00:18:52.400 --> 00:18:56.400
of the world in which we lived or we live in.

351
00:18:56.400 --> 00:18:59.400
So in David's testimony here, he's allowing this brokenness

352
00:18:59.400 --> 00:19:03.400
to be highlighted rather than hidden away.

353
00:19:04.400 --> 00:19:06.400
And so we're gonna see it and we're gonna see a couple

354
00:19:06.400 --> 00:19:08.400
of things as we look at his distress.

355
00:19:08.400 --> 00:19:11.400
We're gonna see the nature of his distress

356
00:19:11.400 --> 00:19:13.400
and then kind of like where it's coming from.

357
00:19:13.400 --> 00:19:18.400
All right, so what does he tell us about his distress here?

358
00:19:18.400 --> 00:19:22.400
Well, he describes it as, you might say intense.

359
00:19:22.400 --> 00:19:25.400
So you look in, at the end of verse two,

360
00:19:25.400 --> 00:19:27.400
he talks about being troubled, but then he gets

361
00:19:27.400 --> 00:19:30.400
to verse three and he says, my soul also is

362
00:19:30.400 --> 00:19:34.400
greatly troubled, but you, oh Lord, how long?

363
00:19:34.400 --> 00:19:37.400
So he's moved from troubled to actually know,

364
00:19:37.400 --> 00:19:40.400
let's intensify this, I'm greatly troubled.

365
00:19:40.400 --> 00:19:44.400
There's a growing intensity. His troubles are severe.

366
00:19:45.400 --> 00:19:49.400
He also tells us that his troubles are relentless.

367
00:19:49.400 --> 00:19:52.400
So he cries out, oh Lord, how long?

368
00:19:52.400 --> 00:19:54.400
So this isn't something that you cry out

369
00:19:54.400 --> 00:19:56.400
just in a moment of difficulty.

370
00:19:56.400 --> 00:19:59.400
This is something you cry out when day after day

371
00:19:59.400 --> 00:20:03.400
or night after night, you're in this distressing situation.

372
00:20:03.400 --> 00:20:06.400
So you're crying out, oh Lord, how long?

373
00:20:06.400 --> 00:20:08.400
This is what David's going through.

374
00:20:08.400 --> 00:20:11.400
He talks about this being night after night in verse six.

375
00:20:11.400 --> 00:20:13.400
He talks about how he's experiencing this

376
00:20:13.400 --> 00:20:15.400
on lots of different fronts.

377
00:20:15.400 --> 00:20:17.400
It's almost like a man drowning and when he comes up

378
00:20:17.400 --> 00:20:19.400
for air then the next wave hits

379
00:20:19.400 --> 00:20:21.400
and then the next wave hits.

380
00:20:21.400 --> 00:20:23.400
This is the relentless situation he's in.

381
00:20:23.400 --> 00:20:27.400
He also talks about the extensiveness of his trouble.

382
00:20:27.400 --> 00:20:30.400
John Calvin, the reformer, once described the book of Psalms

383
00:20:30.400 --> 00:20:34.400
as an anatomy of all parts of the soul.

384
00:20:34.400 --> 00:20:36.400
This is kind of what we see here.

385
00:20:36.400 --> 00:20:39.400
We see trouble hitting David on lots of different fronts.

386
00:20:39.400 --> 00:20:41.400
It's all packed into this one Psalm.

387
00:20:41.400 --> 00:20:45.400
So when he says in verse three, my soul is greatly troubled.

388
00:20:45.400 --> 00:20:47.400
Don't think about that as like differentiating

389
00:20:47.400 --> 00:20:49.400
between like body and spirit.

390
00:20:49.400 --> 00:20:51.400
So what he's saying there, when he's saying my soul

391
00:20:51.400 --> 00:20:54.400
is troubled, he's talking about his whole being.

392
00:20:54.400 --> 00:20:57.400
That's why it's being conveyed by that word.

393
00:20:57.400 --> 00:21:02.400
So all parts of me are experiencing this great distress.

394
00:21:02.400 --> 00:21:05.400
He talks about the physical side of it.

395
00:21:05.400 --> 00:21:08.400
It's debated but he could be suffering from physical illness

396
00:21:08.400 --> 00:21:10.400
as he's writing this Psalm.

397
00:21:10.400 --> 00:21:12.400
So he talks about languishing.

398
00:21:12.400 --> 00:21:14.400
Literally that means he's weak.

399
00:21:14.400 --> 00:21:15.400
He's experiencing weakness.

400
00:21:15.400 --> 00:21:20.400
He prays for healing because of his bones being troubled.

401
00:21:20.400 --> 00:21:22.400
So it could be metaphorically but it could be

402
00:21:22.400 --> 00:21:27.400
he's actually experiencing pain continually in his bones.

403
00:21:27.400 --> 00:21:32.400
He definitely talks about facing death in verse five.

404
00:21:32.400 --> 00:21:33.400
Interesting.

405
00:21:33.400 --> 00:21:35.400
What he says about death, you may have noticed that

406
00:21:35.400 --> 00:21:37.400
and thought, what do we think about that?

407
00:21:37.400 --> 00:21:39.400
For in death there's no remembrance of you.

408
00:21:39.400 --> 00:21:42.400
In shale, who will give you praise?

409
00:21:42.400 --> 00:21:44.400
Let me just say kind of as a sidebar here,

410
00:21:44.400 --> 00:21:46.400
what he's saying here isn't a denial

411
00:21:46.400 --> 00:21:48.400
about what the rest of Scripture teaches

412
00:21:48.400 --> 00:21:51.400
about our existence after death,

413
00:21:51.400 --> 00:21:53.400
about life beyond the grave.

414
00:21:53.400 --> 00:21:55.400
But remember what we're talking about,

415
00:21:55.400 --> 00:21:57.400
our soul, our whole being.

416
00:21:57.400 --> 00:21:58.400
So what does God desire?

417
00:21:58.400 --> 00:22:00.400
God desires that his people praise him

418
00:22:00.400 --> 00:22:02.400
with their whole selves.

419
00:22:02.400 --> 00:22:04.400
And so he's saying, if I die,

420
00:22:04.400 --> 00:22:06.400
if my body goes to the grave,

421
00:22:06.400 --> 00:22:08.400
I won't be able to do that.

422
00:22:08.400 --> 00:22:10.400
So God wants us to praise him with our whole selves

423
00:22:10.400 --> 00:22:12.400
in his creation.

424
00:22:12.400 --> 00:22:19.400
He's saying, Lord, death is going to bring an end to that.

425
00:22:19.400 --> 00:22:22.400
But he also talks about his emotional pain.

426
00:22:22.400 --> 00:22:24.400
He's suffering intense emotional distress.

427
00:22:24.400 --> 00:22:26.400
And actually there's more attention

428
00:22:26.400 --> 00:22:28.400
given to this part of his distress

429
00:22:28.400 --> 00:22:30.400
than anything else within the Psalm.

430
00:22:30.400 --> 00:22:32.400
There's a real emphasis here.

431
00:22:32.400 --> 00:22:35.400
So let's see what he says in verse six again.

432
00:22:35.400 --> 00:22:38.400
He says, I am weary with my moaning.

433
00:22:38.400 --> 00:22:42.400
Every night I flood my bed with tears.

434
00:22:42.400 --> 00:22:44.400
So it's this kind of storm language going on.

435
00:22:44.400 --> 00:22:46.400
I'm flooding my bed with tears.

436
00:22:46.400 --> 00:22:48.400
I drench my couch with weeping.

437
00:22:48.400 --> 00:22:51.400
All right, so David isn't just a little tearful here.

438
00:22:51.400 --> 00:22:54.400
So instead of sleeping, like night after night,

439
00:22:54.400 --> 00:22:56.400
he is weeping.

440
00:22:56.400 --> 00:22:59.400
And his bed is now drenched with tears.

441
00:22:59.400 --> 00:23:04.400
He says, my eye wastes away because of grief.

442
00:23:04.400 --> 00:23:08.400
It grows weak because of all my foes.

443
00:23:08.400 --> 00:23:11.400
So he's got that kind of thousand-yard stare

444
00:23:11.400 --> 00:23:17.400
of a man who has experienced depths of sorrow.

445
00:23:18.400 --> 00:23:22.400
So I love the book of Psalms for many reasons,

446
00:23:22.400 --> 00:23:24.400
but this is one of them because it describes

447
00:23:24.400 --> 00:23:27.400
not just the kind of external troubles we face in life,

448
00:23:27.400 --> 00:23:33.400
but what it feels like to experience those troubles.

449
00:23:33.400 --> 00:23:37.400
And that is just as real and painful

450
00:23:37.400 --> 00:23:40.400
as the physical aspects as well.

451
00:23:40.400 --> 00:23:43.400
And they can be experienced by godly people.

452
00:23:43.400 --> 00:23:46.400
So David is a man after God's own heart,

453
00:23:46.400 --> 00:23:49.400
and yet he experiences these depths of sorrow.

454
00:23:49.400 --> 00:23:52.400
And you can read about this throughout Christian history as well.

455
00:23:52.400 --> 00:23:55.400
I mean, one of my kind of heroes is Charles Spurgeon,

456
00:23:55.400 --> 00:23:59.400
this pastor in the 19th century in London.

457
00:23:59.400 --> 00:24:02.400
And the Lord used him greatly in so many ways.

458
00:24:02.400 --> 00:24:04.400
And he struggled with intense physical pain,

459
00:24:04.400 --> 00:24:08.400
but also severe depression for a lot of his ministry.

460
00:24:08.400 --> 00:24:10.400
But here's what he said,

461
00:24:10.400 --> 00:24:12.400
which ties into what we're looking at here.

462
00:24:12.400 --> 00:24:16.400
The mind can descend far lower than the body,

463
00:24:16.400 --> 00:24:18.400
for in it there are bottomless pits.

464
00:24:18.400 --> 00:24:21.400
The flesh can bear only a certain number of wounds

465
00:24:21.400 --> 00:24:25.400
and no more, but the soul can bleed in ten thousand ways

466
00:24:25.400 --> 00:24:30.400
and die over and over again each hour.

467
00:24:30.400 --> 00:24:34.400
Maybe you know something of that kind of pain,

468
00:24:34.400 --> 00:24:38.400
the tears, the emotional distress that David is describing.

469
00:24:38.400 --> 00:24:43.400
I know I identify with what is being said here.

470
00:24:43.400 --> 00:24:46.400
But there's also a spiritual component.

471
00:24:46.400 --> 00:24:48.400
There's physical distress, emotional distress,

472
00:24:48.400 --> 00:24:50.400
but right out of the gate in the psalm,

473
00:24:50.400 --> 00:24:52.400
he is wrestling with the Lord.

474
00:24:52.400 --> 00:24:55.400
Verse one, he soon cries out,

475
00:24:55.400 --> 00:24:58.400
but you, oh Lord, how long?

476
00:24:58.400 --> 00:25:01.400
Instead of experiencing God's deliverance,

477
00:25:01.400 --> 00:25:05.400
he's experiencing what feels like God's absence

478
00:25:05.400 --> 00:25:09.400
in the midst of these deep sorrows.

479
00:25:09.400 --> 00:25:12.400
So David doesn't just describe his troubles,

480
00:25:12.400 --> 00:25:17.400
he also gives us some clues as to what the source of his trouble might be.

481
00:25:17.400 --> 00:25:19.400
And before we look at those kind of clues

482
00:25:19.400 --> 00:25:21.400
about the source of the trouble,

483
00:25:21.400 --> 00:25:23.400
I just want to acknowledge that

484
00:25:23.400 --> 00:25:27.400
that is a really difficult subject to even bring up.

485
00:25:27.400 --> 00:25:29.400
Like if you've got a sprained ankle,

486
00:25:29.400 --> 00:25:32.400
it's easy to identify, oh, you're experiencing pain in your ankle?

487
00:25:32.400 --> 00:25:34.400
Well, it's sprained.

488
00:25:34.400 --> 00:25:36.400
Let's raise that up and let it rest

489
00:25:36.400 --> 00:25:40.400
and so you can identify the source of the pain and deal with it.

490
00:25:40.400 --> 00:25:42.400
But it's not always that straightforward

491
00:25:42.400 --> 00:25:45.400
when it comes to emotional distress.

492
00:25:45.400 --> 00:25:49.400
And sometimes it can be a reaction to a specific loss,

493
00:25:49.400 --> 00:25:51.400
but I know I've been through seasons

494
00:25:51.400 --> 00:25:53.400
where I could not tell you for the life of me

495
00:25:53.400 --> 00:25:56.400
why I feel so low.

496
00:25:56.400 --> 00:25:59.400
You can't point to the source of that.

497
00:25:59.400 --> 00:26:02.400
And it can be even harder to work through thinking through that

498
00:26:02.400 --> 00:26:09.400
when you're in the disorienting fog of this kind of distress

499
00:26:09.400 --> 00:26:11.400
being described here in the Psalm.

500
00:26:11.400 --> 00:26:13.400
And by the way, that's one of the many reasons

501
00:26:13.400 --> 00:26:15.400
why we shouldn't suffer in silence.

502
00:26:15.400 --> 00:26:18.400
Why it's important to, you know, as Caleb just shared,

503
00:26:18.400 --> 00:26:20.400
just being open and vulnerable with one another

504
00:26:20.400 --> 00:26:23.400
because we need one another in this.

505
00:26:23.400 --> 00:26:25.400
And this Psalm, like the other Psalms,

506
00:26:25.400 --> 00:26:27.400
this is corporate worship here.

507
00:26:27.400 --> 00:26:30.400
We're praying this together. We're lamenting together.

508
00:26:30.400 --> 00:26:36.400
So there's a togetherness when it comes to our grief that we need.

509
00:26:36.400 --> 00:26:39.400
So open up and let's weep together

510
00:26:39.400 --> 00:26:43.400
and see what we can do to come alongside one another.

511
00:26:43.400 --> 00:26:46.400
That being said, all that being said, that kind of caveat there,

512
00:26:46.400 --> 00:26:48.400
David wrestles with the source of his problem.

513
00:26:48.400 --> 00:26:51.400
He talks about his enemies in verses 7 to 10.

514
00:26:51.400 --> 00:26:54.400
We see that he's surrounded by enemies.

515
00:26:54.400 --> 00:26:57.400
They certainly factor into the trouble that he is experiencing.

516
00:26:57.400 --> 00:26:59.400
They are on the attack.

517
00:26:59.400 --> 00:27:04.400
It seems like they're even gloating over what David is experiencing.

518
00:27:04.400 --> 00:27:07.400
And like David's enemies, sometimes there are external factors

519
00:27:07.400 --> 00:27:13.400
beyond our control that kind of pull the rug out from underneath us.

520
00:27:13.400 --> 00:27:16.400
And we didn't see it coming, but there it is.

